<fr:p>This proposition also applies to simplicial objects in other categories <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {C}]]></fr:tex> apart from that of topological spaces; it suffices that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathscr {C}]]></fr:tex> satisfy the following:

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2496</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-iii-6.2.4.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-6.2.4.1.xml</fr:route><fr:authors /><fr:number>6.2.4.1</fr:number></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Finite projective limits exist in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>.
        Finite projective sums exist in <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>, and they are disjoint and universal.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:p></fr:mainmatter>
